Description: Xcode 26.5 SDK cleaned transitive includes; postgis uses INT_MIN /
INT_MAX in postgis/gserialized_typmod.c (line ~306) but never includes <limits.h>,
relying on it being pulled in through <stdio.h>. Under the 26.5 SDK this breaks:
  error: use of undeclared identifier 'INT_MIN' / 'INT_MAX'
Confirmed still broken in postgis 3.5.4 / 3.5.7 / 3.6.4 / main, so upgrading does
not help; <limits.h> is a standard C header and harmless everywhere.

--- a/postgis/gserialized_typmod.c
+++ b/postgis/gserialized_typmod.c
@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@
 #include <float.h>
 #include <string.h>
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <errno.h>
+#include <limits.h>
 
 #include "utils/elog.h"
